The `swizzle` function rearranges the components of a vector. It takes a vector `v` and four compile-time constants representing the new order of components. The function uses Zig's `@shuffle` intrinsic to create a new vector with the specified component order. Here is the code example:

```zig
pub inline fn swizzle(
    v: Vec4f,
    comptime x: Vec4fComponent,
    comptime y: Vec4fComponent,
    comptime z: Vec4fComponent,
    comptime w: Vec4fComponent,
) Vec4f {
    return @shuffle(f32, v, undefined, [4]i32{@intFromEnum(x), @intFromEnum(y), @intFromEnum(z), @intFromEnum(w)});
}
```

