The `quatFromAxisAngle` method constructs a quaternion from an axis and an angle. It normalizes the input axis, calculates half the angle, computes sine and cosine of this half-angle, and then assembles the quaternion components accordingly.

```zig
pub fn quatFromAxisAngle(axis: Vec3f, angle: f32) Quat {
	const normal = normalize(axis);
	const n = Vec4f{normal[0], normal[1], normal[2], 1.0};
	const a = angle*0.5;
	const sc: [2]f32 = .{@sin(a), @cos(a)};
	return .{.q = n*Vec4f{sc[0], sc[0], sc[0], sc[1]}};
}
```
